title: Protests against Trump's immigration ban: in pictures
text:
Previous slide Next slide 1 of 22 View All Skip Ad 
President Donald Trump's travel ban barring citizens of seven predominantly Muslim nations entry into the U.S. has sparked protests around the country on Saturday night and Sunday morning. Protesters who gathered at Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport Saturday evening, pictured, voiced their displeasure with Trump's executive order. The crowd of a few dozen ballooned into hundreds of demonstrators who frequently chanted "Set them free!" At times, cheers erupted from the crowd as those who were detained got released. Credit: G. Morty Ortega/Getty Images
